= Equipment

== Weapons
Weapons have a fixe damage die; magical version will add some rider benefits. Speciality can increase this dice size. This damage die also, as unless otherwise specified, is the standard unit used in dice pool.


#table(
  columns: (1fr, 2fr, 1fr),
  [*Name*], [*Description*], [*Damage*],
  // Example row
  // [Sword], [A classic blade], [1d8], [Melee], [Versatile],
  [1H Melee Weapon], [Short sword, a mace, a dagger], [1d6],
  [2H Melee Weapon], [Long sword, a battle axe], [1d10],
  [1H Ranged Weapon], [a sling, a dart gun], [1d4],
  [2H Ranged Weapon], [a bow, a crossbow], [1d8],
)

== Armors
Armors usage requires Training that come from specialty. They reduce the damage taken by a fixed amount, and can have some rider benefits.

#table(
  columns: (1fr, 2fr, 1fr, ),
  [*Name*], [*Description*], [*Defense*],
  // Example row
  // [Leather Armor], [Light protective gear], [+2], [Light], [Flexible],
  [Light Armor], [Leather armor, padded armor], [+1],
  [Medium Armor], [Chain mail, scale mail], [+2],
  [Heavy Armor], [Plate mail, splint mail], [+3],
  [Shield], [A sturdy shield], [+2], [Versatile],
)


